<div class="xar-mod-head">
    <span class="xar-mod-title">
        <xar:mlstring>SiteSearch - Databases</xar:mlstring>
    </span>
</div>
<div class="xar-mod-body">

    <form method="post" action="#xarModURL('sitesearch', 'admin', 'databases')#">
        <input type="hidden" name="authid" id="authid" value="#$authid#" />

        <p>
            Databases allow you to seperate you content allowing for searching to be done on any one or all of the databases.  This allows for directed searches.
        </p>
        <p>
            For each database you must specify a indexer to get content to be inserted into the database.  Currently there are 3 indexers provided. Indexers normally match up to a module.  There are indexers for articles, julian, and movies modules.  You can also specify arguments and mapping for each database indexer pair.
        </p>
        <p>
            Here is an example:
            <pre>
                articles:articles:Articles DB
                =args
                    =itemtype:news
                =mappings
            </pre>
        </p>
        
        <fieldset>
            <legend>Databases</legend>        
            
            <div class="xar-form-wrapper">        
                <label class="xar-form-label"><xar:mlstring>Databases:</xar:mlstring></label>
                <textarea name="limits" class="xar-form-textareaxlarge"><xar:var name="limits" /></textarea>
            </div>
    
            <div class="xar-form-wrapper-after">
                <input type="submit" name="update" value="#xarML('Update')#" />
            </div>
        </fieldset>
                
    </form>  
           
</div>